###
### file_contexts — labels for paths the Milady on-device agent owns.
###
### NOTE: Android's installd does NOT consult this file when labeling
### files inside /data/data/<pkg>/. installd assigns
### `app_data_file` (or `privapp_data_file` for privileged apps) based
### on seapp_contexts, regardless of what we say here.
###
### These entries become load-bearing if a future build re-introduces
### a custom seinfo + domain transition (see milady_agent.te). At that
### point MiladyAgentService.relabelAgentTree() can call
### `SELinux.restoreconRecursive("/data/data/.../files/agent")` and
### the kernel will use the patterns below to apply the agent-specific
### types declared in milady_agent.te.
###
### Until then, installd's `app_data_file` label is the effective one
### and the `allow platform_app app_data_file:file execute` rule in
### milady_agent.te is what makes the bun execve actually work.
###

# Bundled binary tree (bun + musl loader + libstdc++ + libgcc + libllama).
/data/data/com\.miladyai\.milady/files/agent/x86_64(/.*)?      u:object_r:milady_agent_exec:s0
/data/data/com\.miladyai\.milady/files/agent/arm64-v8a(/.*)?   u:object_r:milady_agent_exec:s0

# Agent state + bundle (anything else under files/agent/ that isn't a binary).
/data/data/com\.miladyai\.milady/files/agent(/.*)?             u:object_r:milady_agent_data:s0
/data/data/com\.miladyai\.milady/files/\.milady(/.*)?          u:object_r:milady_agent_data:s0
